OCRopus - open source document analysis and OCR system (www.ocropus.org)

Version 0.1.1 (2007-10-31)


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Building OCRopus
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Please refer to the file INSTALL for help on building OCRopus from 
source.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Executing OCRopus
------------------------------------------------------------------------
After successfully building ocropus you can use "ocrocmd/ocrocmd" for
performing OCR on a document image (preferably in .png format).
Try e.g.
    ocrocmd/ocrocmd data/pages/alice_1.png

But, OCRopus can do more than ocrocmd shows:

If you have built ocroscript you get an interpreter with the complete
OCRopus
functionality. You can run this either with an appropriate Lua script or 
in
interactive mode. The OCRopus team is actually using ocroscript for 
quick
development and unit testing.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Documentation
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Please refer to http://www.ocropus.org/wiki/DocumentationIndex
for the most recent documentation of OCRopus.


